## Option 1 — Open Source License (CERN-OHL-S-2.0)

**Use this option if:**
- You are a researcher, student, or hobbyist
- You are building an open-source hardware project
- You are willing to open-source your derivative work under the same
  CERN-OHL-S-2.0 license

**Terms:** See the full CERN-OHL-S-2.0 text in `LICENSE-OHL.txt`
(or visit https://cern-ohl.org/s/v2.0).

Key obligations under this license:
- ✅ You may use, study, modify, and distribute the Work
- ✅ You may manufacture and distribute physical products based on the Work
- ❌ You MUST open-source any derivative work under CERN-OHL-S-2.0
- ❌ You MUST provide the full source (RTL, RTL testbenches, gate-level
  netlists, and any software necessary to operate or modify the design)
- ❌ You MUST include attribution to the original author
- ❌ You CANNOT use the Work in a closed-source commercial product
  without obtaining Option 2 below

