## Frequently Asked Questions

**Q: Can I use Titan X5-B in my company's product for free under
   CERN-OHL-S-2.0?**

A: Only if your product is fully open-source under a compatible
   reciprocal license. If your product is closed-source, you must
   obtain the Commercial License.

**Q: Can I modify Titan X5-B and sell the modified version?**

A: Under CERN-OHL-S-2.0, yes, but you must open-source your
   modifications. To sell closed-source modifications, you need the
   Commercial License.

**Q: Can I use Titan X5-B for teaching at a university?**

A: Yes, the open-source license permits educational use.

**Q: How do I get the Commercial License?**

A: Email the author. After signing a mutual NDA, you will receive
   a license agreement tailored to your use case (perpetual,
   subscription, or buyout).

**Q: I'm a startup with no budget. Can I get a discount?**

A: Yes. The author offers startup discounts and deferred-payment
   arrangements for early-stage companies. Reach out to discuss.

